        "rich_text_4iaLXd": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "1st para",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Rings have long served as powerful symbols of love, commitment, and tradition across cultures. Among the most significant of these are the <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/engagement-rings\" title=\"Engagement Rings\">Engagement Ring</a> and the <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/wedding-rings\" title=\"Wedding Rings\">Wedding Ring</a>, the two pieces of jewellery that often look similar but carry very different meanings and histories. While both are deeply connected to the journey of marriage, they mark distinct moments in a couple’s relationship. Understanding the differences between them not only helps in choosing the right rings but also adds deeper value to what they represent. </p><p>At Lucira, we believe every love story deserves sparkle. Whether you're exploring Lab Grown Diamond Rings for a proposal or planning your dream wedding, here's a guide to help you understand the key differences between Engagement and Wedding Rings, and when each one makes its special appearance.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_nFzXrC": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "name": "What is an engagement ring?",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Lucira_product_lot_2_35219_Wedding_Ring.jpg",
            "text": "<h2>What Is an Engagement Ring?</h2><p>An Engagement Ring, at its core, represents a promise to spend your life with your partner and is given during the proposal. The ring serves as a visual and emotional reminder of that decision and is often seen as a public declaration of love and commitment.</p><p>Engagement rings are known for their eye-catching designs and grand centre stones. Generally more elaborate than a Wedding Ring, Engagement Rings feature a prominent centre diamond with a <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/engagement-rings-solitaire\" title=\"Solitaire Engagement RIngs\">solitaire</a> or halo setting. Worn on the ring finger, this ring holds the memory of a promise. The most classic and popular style features a single diamond, but there is a wide range of options to suit different tastes and budgets.</p><p>Lucira’s Lab Grown Diamond Engagement Rings are designed to offer all the brilliance of mined diamonds at a fraction of the cost and with zero environmental guilt. A beautiful choice to celebrate a beautiful relationship.</p>",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "engagement",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_Xd3hL7": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "name": "What Is a Wedding Ring?",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Lucira_product_33957_Wedding_Ring.jpg",
            "text": "<h2>What Is a Wedding Ring?</h2><p>A Wedding Ring, most often a wedding band, is exchanged between both partners during the wedding ceremony. It symbolizes the formal, legal, and spiritual bond of marriage, a lasting commitment to partnership, fidelity, and shared life. Unlike an Engagement Ring, which signifies a proposal and is usually adorned with a central gemstone, the Wedding Ring is often more understated in design, focusing on simplicity, elegance, and everyday wearability.</p><p>Wedding Rings come in various styles, and today’s couples often choose bands that reflect their personal tastes, daily comfort, and how well the ring complements the Engagement Ring. Apart from the classic wedding band, you can also go for <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/wedding-rings-stackable\" title=\"Stackable Wedding Rings\">stackable wedding rings</a>, which are slender bands designed to be worn alongside the Engagement Ring or even layered with other bands over time, like anniversary rings or milestone bands. <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/wedding-rings-eternity\" title=\"Eternity RIngs\">Eternity rings</a> are also a great choice for wedding bands with a continuous circle of Lab Grown Diamonds around the ring. </p>",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "wedding",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_QiLnek": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "name": "Do You Need Both?",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/VS.jpg",
            "text": "<h2>Do You Need Both?</h2><p>You don’t necessarily need both, but many couples choose both for emotional and aesthetic reasons. The engagement ring marks the beginning of your journey, while the wedding ring seals the bond forever. Together, they tell your full love story.</p><p>Post-wedding, it's common to wear both the engagement ring and the wedding ring on the same finger. Traditionally, the wedding ring is placed first, so it sits closer to the heart, followed by the engagement ring. </p><p>At Lucira, we offer exquisite collections of both Engagement and Wedding Rings, crafted with Lab Grown Diamonds that are certified, sustainable, and stunning. Whether you’re planning the perfect proposal or preparing to say \"I do,\" we’re here to help you find rings that reflect your values and your love.</p><p>Ready to begin your forever? Explore Lucira’s curated collection of Lab Grown Engagement and Wedding Rings here.</p>",
            "reverse_layout": true,
            "custom_id": "both",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        }
